-- U.S. Senate approves Burwell as health secretary
-- By Emily Stephenson
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 02:09PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, June 5 (Reuters) - The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed Sylvia Mathews Burwell as President Barack Obama's new health secretary, a post that makes her chiefly responsible for implementing the controversial healthcare law known as Obamacare.

